{"title": "Humble Attempt to Promote Explicit Agreement and Visible Union of God's People in Extraordinary Prayer, . . .", "description": "Not only does this powerful little piece of writing contain within its pages the timely exhortation to Christians to pray at just such a time as this for our Lord's kingdom to come (as relevant today as it was in 1747), but we're also given a good dose of eschatology and a taste of history to boot--almost forgotten knowledge, if you will. A refreshing, eye-opening, inspirational piece of work. (FYI: \"extraordinary prayer\" can be defined as \"prayer with special purpose,\" and a \"concert of prayer\" is an agreement of two or more in a prayer plan.)    - Summary by Debra Bridgford", "duration": 20706, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "140", "name": "Jonathan Edwards"}], "coverArt": null, "copyright_year": "1789", "genres": ["Christianity - Other"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Debra Bridgford"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Debra Bridgford"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Lynne T"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "InTheDesert"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Preface by a Former English Editor", "readers": [20310], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/humbleattempt_2511_librivox/humbleattempt_00_edwards_64kb.mp3", "duration": 250}, {"section": 1, "title": "Explanatory Introduction", "readers": [20310], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/humbleattempt_2511_librivox/humbleattempt_01_edwards_64kb.mp3", "duration": 434}, {"section": 2, "title": "Observations on the Text", "readers": [20310], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/humbleattempt_2511_librivox/humbleattempt_02_edwards_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1145}, {"section": 3, "title": "An Historical Account of the Concert to Which the Memorial Relates", "readers": [20310], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/humbleattempt_2511_librivox/humbleattempt_03_edwards_64kb.mp3", "duration": 675}, {"section": 4, "title